/wiki/Josephine_Tomic: Josephine Tomic ( born 9 June 1989 ) is an Australian track cyclist . She has been selected to represent Australia at the 2012 Summer Olympics in the Team Pursuit .
/wiki/Shara_Gillow: Shara Gillow ( born 23 December 1987 ) is an Australian cyclist , who currently rides for UCI Women 's WorldTeam FDJ Nouvelle-Aquitaine Futuroscope . She was selected to represent Australia at the 2012 Summer Olympics , where she finished 13th in the time trial and 39th in the road race .
/wiki/Sarah_Kent_(cyclist): Sarah Kent ( born ( 1990-02-10 ) 10 February 1990 ) is an Australian female track cyclist . She won the bronze medal in the team pursuit event at the 2009 UCI Track Cycling World Championships . She also competed in at the 2010 and 2011 UCI Track Cycling World Championships .
/wiki/Tiffany_Cromwell: Tiffany Jane Cromwell ( born 6 July 1988 ) is an Australian road cyclist , who currently rides for UCI Women 's WorldTeam Canyon-SRAM . In November 2015 she was announced as part of the Canyon-SRAM team 's inaugural squad for the 2016 season .
/wiki/Lauren_Kitchen: Lauren Kitchen ( born 21 November 1990 ) is an Australian professional racing cyclist , who currently rides for UCI Women 's WorldTeam FDJ Nouvelle-Aquitaine Futuroscope . A female road cyclist from New South Wales , Australia , Kitchen is currently studying a Bachelor of Planning at the University of NSW in Sydney part-time as well as cycling for NSW and Australia at local , interstate and international events . In September 2016 she was announced as part of the WM3 Pro Cycling squad for 2017 .
/wiki/Amy_Cure: Amy Louise Cure ( born 31 December 1992 ) is an Australian professional track cyclist . She cycles for Team Jayco-AIS . She has set several world records . She won a junior world championship race in 2009 , and represented Australia at the 2012 Summer Olympics . She is the first person in history to medal at every endurance track event at world championship level ; with three newly gained medals in the team pursuit , omnium , and madison at 2017 UCI Track Cycling World Championships in Hong Kong . While she was considered as a typical Tasmanian type of racer- never gives up attitude during the race , she was considered as the latest cycling talent in Tasmania as legendary 5 time world champions Danny Clark , Olympic gold medallist Michael Grenda and road cyclist Richie Porte .
/wiki/Carlee_Taylor: Carlee Taylor ( born 15 February 1989 ) is an Australian racing cyclist . She took up cycling in 2007 after previously competing in triathlon .
/wiki/Jessica_Allen_(Australian_cyclist): Jessica Allen ( born 17 April 1993 ) is an Australian professional racing cyclist , who currently rides for UCI Women 's WorldTeam Mitchelton-Scott .
/wiki/Jenelle_Crooks: Jenelle Crooks ( born 2 July 1994 ) is an Australian professional racing cyclist , who currently rides for UCI Women 's Continental Team Tibco-Silicon Valley Bank . Crooks has also competed for Australian National Road Series team Specialized Women 's Racing and with the Australian National Team for their tour of European races .
/wiki/Ellen_Skerritt: Ellen Skerritt ( born 20 December 1994 ) is an Australian professional racing cyclist who rides for Alé-Cipollini .
/wiki/Alexandra_Manly: Alexandra Manly ( born 28 February 1996 ) is an Australian professional racing cyclist , who last rode for UCI Women 's Team Mitchelton-Scott . Manly was born in Kalgoorlie , Western Australia , but now lives in South Australia . Before taking up cycling , Manly had previously tried basketball , cross country running , netball , hockey , tennis , javelin , and steeple chase .
/wiki/Sarah_Gigante: Sarah Gigante ( born 6 October 2000 ) is an Australian racing cyclist , who currently rides for UCI Women 's Continental Team Tibco-Silicon Valley Bank .
